                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d879">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/8641: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Beaulac</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-01-18T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 18, 1940—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4. Your despatch no. 2715, January 15. The Department perceives no objection
                    whatever to your making clear its position, as expressed in the Department’s
                    telegram no. 3, January 13, 5 p.m., to anyone in your discretion, and
                    specifically to the persons mentioned in your despatch under reference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
